caption: Disappointed in Paula's Thai Kitchen. While the quality of food was some of the best I have had in Chicago, the prices were ASTRONOMICALLY high and completely out of proportion to the quality and portion size. There are other places in the city with comparable quality where you can get at least double the amount of food for the cost. :/
(Translated by Google) Delicious in Thai style .. Zabs Lai Lovely staff  (Original) อร่อยแบบไทยแท้..แซ่บส์หลาย พนักงานน่ารัก
Great customer service.  The food was beyond  amazing.
It was such a cool place! Great food and amazing service. The servers were really attentive and it was a cool vibe

Ordered takeout from Paula's tonight and the food was severely disappointing. The one positive was the food was hot and of good temperature, but the pad Thai  tasted terribly bland, overly sweet, and the texture of it seemed like it must have been sitting for far too long as it was completely congealed. The green curry tasted ok, but also wasn't as good as we hoped. In the past, I have enjoyed eating at Paula's in their dining area, but after this experience I do not think I would order out from there anytime soon.
I always get the shrimp Tom Yum soup extra spicy 🔥🥵 so good definitely 5 stars
Authentic thai but not the best with the fancy price
Delicious every time.

Ordered a take out for chicken pad thai, it was so dry and bland. The chicken was probably cooked at least a half day ago, it had bad smell to it. I had to throw away the whole thing after having a bite. The portion size was so little too.
Thai food at this location - very tasty. it was so appetizing. i will probably become a regular. the bill was appropriate.

YOU GUYS must try this place! Their green curry chicken was other worldly. WOW, i haven't found one this good in a while. Their to-go service is excellent and they wrap the food so well as to prevent sauce spillage. Love it.

(Translated by Google) Famous restaurant in Chicago Recommended for those who like Thai food, spicy, authentic Thai food, flavorful dishes. Recommended dishes Papaya Salad with Crab and Fermented Fish Get the mood like eating in Thailand If medium spicy, then it is considered very spicy for Thai people. As for people who like seafood. Recommended squid and lemon. Squid is not fishy Sometimes go get squid and egg too ^^ Crispy pork kale is delicious. Eating with hot rice, it is very pleasing to have a friend from Thailand. Authentic Thai food.  Very good.

Last week was our first time we came to that excellent restaurant. But It is surely not the last time. We passed a splendid evening with the generous service, with the first-rate  cuisine and booze and with the honest charge. We will absolutely visit there soon.

Look no further if you're looking for a truely authentic Thai restaurant! I'm from Thailand, and this place makes me feel like I'm back home. Food was fresh and of great portions as well!
Good food! Good price!

This tiny little place is really delicious and serves good food at a very decent price. Come here for your familiar Thai favorites. Not the same Thai food you'd get in Thailand but it's delicious and decent value too.
Very authentic resturant with great food and great experience. We always order something else and prob tried the entire menu already :) Everything is delicious! #SweepstakeEntry
Food is ok, price is definitely higher than other Thai restaurants. Often need extra 10 mins to get the food if ordering take out

Authentic Thai food!
My number 2 thai spot in Chicago!

What a good surprise!! We didn’t know the place and went there without expectation. We ordered classic items: chicken satay, e-san sausages, Tom kha soup as hot pot, crispy pat Thai and a fried rice. All dishes were well seasoned and tasted really good!!
Delicious pork belly papaya salad and pad see ew.  Small and cozy.

Solid spot, but using broccoli stems instead of crowns for their pad sie ewe was so extraordinarily disappointing. I’ve never seen that done before ever, and it really ruined the magic of the dish. Quite a small place. Prices are more than fair tho. However, the broccoli thing, oy, PTK please bring the crowns back.
This place is a real gem.  The food is the best thai food in Chicago. That said, the service can been poor and the spice levels are inconsistent.
Love the food. The location is very small so I recommend take out. Sometimes the spicy levels do vary.

This place is an unassuming place, however the food is mindblowing. Some of the best thai food in Chicago. Went there several times while staying there. And the staff is very friendly. Definitely go there.
The food there was amazing...
Fast service and lovely food
I tasted mine and my dates dish and both were uuuumm good. I had issue with walking through and viewing the kitchen to pee. don't enjoy seeing the under belly.

One the best places to have authentic thai in chicago i would say!! I tried the veggie dumplings and chicken satay. The taste and flavors were exactly as i had remembered it to be when i had thai for the first time in irving texas. Basil fried rice was a bomb... i loved the entire experience !! The waiter in particular was extremely courteous and pleasant.

The food is great don't get me wrong but their service is a little bit trash I mean tables were not bussed and the waitress had black on with a very visible stain on her clothing and it was rush service as well I just felt it would have been better service at flattop or even freaking dave n buster's for that matter but oh well I guess

This is one of the best Thai eatery i have been to. I am from new jersey and i went on a trip  to Chicago. Was looking for good food late night around 11 when i discovered this Gem. The food was authentic home cooked Thai food which exceeded my expectations in all ways. Kudos to the home chefs and the service was extra oridnary. Keep up the great work.
It was hot. My fried rice had some kick to it.
Incredible food! And reasonably priced.

I've been to Paula's multiple times now and it has been the best Thai I've had in the city. The woman who waits us every time is a serious hard worker. Every dish I've had, take in or carry out, has been phenomenal! 10/10 recommend.

There are a brunch of thai food restaurant in the neighborhood, but this one is by far the best - the food is super authentic, like you would find in Northern Thailand. Ask them for their specials - you won't regret it! Our favorites include the crispy rice with nam sausage, basil thai, mango sticky rice and the crispy pork belly which are all amazing.

Excellent food! Very flavourful, made to order, and FILLING!  They will adjust the amount of heat/spice as needed, the waitress is very attentive (my water glass was empty for less than a minute, then she was refilling it), and the food is perfectly cooked.  They don't have WiFi or a public bathroom (there simply isn't one in the restaurant, so don't get grumpy or pushy - it's an old building and they don't have a bathroom).
Very good food and great service. Open late night.

Been here like 5-6 times. It was great and authentic. But in my 2nd to last visit, I am very disappointed. The taste change its not as good  as before. I am not sure of they change the chefs. I wish they can make hood food again.
I love this place. The food is awesome, I will comeback here again. I wish they could have delivery services, it a little bit far from downtown.
Fresh quick Thai food dishes and inexpensive.
It's a hole in the wall that offers good northern thai food! Spicy food galore! The mango and sticky rice was what I liked best.
Great real northern Thai food spicy options keep that water close at hand small place not many seats I would say about 25  bring your own byob

I didn’t leave a review before but for the second time already, I ordered a dish not spicy and it came with crushed fresh chili. The girl argued that the sauce is always like that. No it’s not because I frequent this restaurant because it’s close to me and I always get the same dish and the previous times they got it right.
Consistently good food!
Very kind service and good pad Thai.
Very good place to eat

The service here was nice and the restraint was clean and we'll put together. The food was phenomenal with the perfect amount of spice.  I went with my family and we asked for our noodles to be extra spicy and they definitely delivered! The food was cooked and seasoned well. I had the Boat Noddles and I can say that I will definitely be returning for another bowl. The meat was tender and packed with flavors. My father ordered the curry and definitely enjoyed the zing it had. He did have get another cup of water by the end of the meal (due to the spice) but happily enjoyed his meal. Prices were relatively low and and it is a good place for college kids to frequent. I would definitely recommend this if you want a good meal that is quick and easy as well as affordable .

We had a great meal and would love to go back later in the future. We ordered green papaya salad, garlic scallops, and tiger cry. All of them were excellent and authentic. There are still many more exciting items to try on the special menu and all the curry dishes.  There is another Thai-ish restaurant next door but I would say Paula’s is way more authentic and flavorful than the Joyee like American Asian food. Give Paula’s a try. Won’t regret it.
Best thai food in the town! You must call the restaurant in advance to make reservation or make sure that they are open. Tiger cry, beef hot pot, pad thai were so delicious!
Best somtum in Chicago.

The food was good!!! I ordered a spicy veggie curry and it was spicy. If you like a good kick in your food this is a place worth trying. The space is small so if you go when it's crowded you'll have to wait. The customer service is good. The employees were friendly and helpful.
I had decided I would never be able to find Thai food as good as I used to get in Singapore/Thailand. All that has changed. Best Thai food in the United States that's I've been able to find
Really liked food at this place. Real Thai food I say:)))
Very good food and cheap!

caption: (Translated by Google) I used to work at an autentic Thai restaurant and I tried to find a similar taste in America. However, I tried this restaurant, it was very authentic and delicious. I could tell they put lots of effort for all their ingredients!! For example, the lemongrass and galangal were cooked softer so I could actually chew it unlike other restaurants!!! Ask them to make your food spicy. It is very spicy just as much as you can get in Thailand!!! There aren't many places that traditionally taste like this and are spicy and delicious in Thai restaurants in the United States, but this restaurant has a variety of menus and it's really great!! I was surprised to find that what I ate at this restaurant was much more delicious than the tom yang dream and pad thai I had in Thailand!! ^__^ I hope you enjoy it!! My husband and I LOVE Paula's. We've compared all the Thai restaurants in LP and they win hands down. They have more authentic items on the menu than other places and they always get our spicy level request just right!!!!! The raw shrimp salad is bomb!!!!!
Excellent food and great service.
This place is absolutely delicious!! We loved the food and experience,  service was excellent!!

After living in Thailand for 3 years, I've been let down by Thai food in the US/Chicago but Paula's Thai Kitchen has absolutely restored my faith in Chicago's Thai food scene. It's one of the very rare places in Chicago that serves authentic, regional Thai food and it's very tasty.  The dining room isn't anything special but the food is amazing. Keep in mind that authentic Thai food is very spicy and some dishes have a strong aroma. That may not be for everyone hence a few bad review but most restaurants do to Thai food what Taco Bell does to Mexican food and Paula's does not so kudos to the chef :-)
Delicious authentic Thai food if you know how to order real Thai food.
Man, this place has good food. I recommend the red curry! I will be coming back.
If you're looking for spicy Thai food(eastern) style? This place is the must!

They had no soy sauce which I found odd for a Thai place, but I thought no big deal...until I got home and tasted my thai fried rice dinner which was the most bland food I have ever eaten.  Also, their crab ragoon was horrible.
Good food as for my taste. Curry was simply perfect
A cute little homely restaurant with good service. Not much to offer for vegetarians but what little we did have was quite delicious - the potato chive pan fried dumplings as well as the green curry.
Without doubt the best, authentic, Thai food in Chicago, well worth the visit if you get the chance
The food was really good and our waitress was very nice!
Generous 2 star, Tom Yum soup is no good, old nasty smelling lemongrass couldn't even eat the chicken the soup was to nasty fishy smell, not like normal tom yum soup.
Delicious chicken green curry and steamed post stickers! Great service and prices. Highly recommend.
Amazing food! Hits all the perfect notes, service is great and so nice. Couldn't ask for better food or ambiance.
Yo closed at 1:30... says 2 on the door.. and online
loved it
Delicious meals
Amazing curry - some of the best I've ever had (panang with chicken is my usual). A total mom and pop joint that's BYOB and feels like you're dining in someone's own home. Love this spot!

This place is in the heart of Depaul area. It's a small place, maybe 5 tables, tops. I believe they do most of their business through carryout or delivery. There were 4 of us for dinner. The meals were ample, we were all able to share what we had with each other. I rather enjoyed, nothing spectacular about it, just good basic Thai food. The place is BYOB, and the accept credit cards. My biggest issue with the place was a feeling cramped. A table for 4 , pushed back against the wall, with the other two seats in the only aisle the restaurant had. I wanted to go to the bathroom, but decided not to, when I could not find it, and it almost appeared that would have to go through the kitchen to get there. I could definitely go back for the food, but ambiance is a deterrent.

I lived in Thailand for 10 years.  This is REAL authentic Thai food.  For the people giving this place a bad rap, they've probably never eaten anything other than Pad Thai and don't know a thing about Thai cuisine.  Please go somewhere else, this is a small boutique restaurant catering to those wanting an authentic Thai cuisine experience, not that bland, sweetened Americanized crap certain "Thai" restaurants in Chicago like to pass off as Thai food.  I don't want this place to change a thing.  Thanks!
I guess I can follow a youtube video and cook better Thai food than this restaurant. Not to mention it took them more than 75 minutes  for delivery Look for another restaurant to eat at
It took 45 minutes for Pad Thai shrimp unbelievable what an epic waste of time never go to this place and the guy who said it smells like wet dog he's right total blowout never again

Very fresh and delicious. A laid back Thai spot. I definitely recommend this place. Give it a try before eating at places where the noodles are ready and they only heat and mix it with other ingredients. Food is made to order here!

I'm very excited that no one else has reviewed this "restaurant" so that I can become the voice of reason should anyone luckily choose to check the reviews before making the drunk mistake I did. A wonderful night at a nearby blues club unfortunately placed me in the path of this soon to be forcefully removed eatery. All I can say is, DONT EAT ANYTHING. Be careful to even breathe the air. Seriously, where do I begin? We ordered to basil leaf chicken and sesame chicken, and I was hit with regret before my butt even hit the uncomfortable chair I waited in. The entire establishment smells like wet dog. I watched a "dine in" customer walk through the kitchen to use the bathroom. When we finally got our food I was so eager to breathe fresh air that I didn't even notice we were overcharged. And honestly, regardless of what the menu says, one dollar would be overcharged for anything. I am a stingy man. I'm not proud to admit it, but I brought my business back to my local late night Chinese place after they got a 46 on their health exam, because you just can't beat 3 pounds of food laced in MSG for 8 bucks. Even so, I swear to you, based on smell and appearance alone I made the executive decision on behalf of my body to throw Paula's entire order away. That was the best decision I made all night. Please do yourself a favor and eat anything else. Or just give the money to a homeless person. But please tell them not to spend it at Paula's.
